condition.narrative: For the purposes of implementing Part 2 of the Project, and not later than three (3) months after the Effectiveness Date or anyother date acceptable to the Association, the Recipient shall prepare and adopt a BPC Operations Manual in form and substanceacceptable to theAssociation, giving details of the guidelines and procedures governing the business plan competition activitiesand BPC Grants under the Project, including (i) the selection, prioritization and eligibility criteria for financing of start-upsand existing enterprises with high potential for growth; (ii) business plan competition guidelines; (iii) procedures for the awardof BPC Grants and selection of BPC Beneficiaries; (iv) amounts of BPC Grants to be paid on a non-reimbursable basis; and (v) theconditions for release of the BPC Grant. Except as the Association shall otherwise agree, the Recipient shall not amend, waive orfail to enforce the BPC Operations Manual, or any provisions thereof. In case of any conflict between the provisions of the BPCOperations Manual and those of this Agreement, the provisions of this Agreement shall prevail.
The PCU shall, not later than four (4) months after the Effective Date, appoint two Project accountants, with qualifications,experience and under terms of reference acceptable to the Association.
